commit message:
Updated support list: Google Nexus 7 (2013) has no MF Classic support.

See: http://www.nfcbrief.com/2013/08/google-completes-broadcom-transition.html
Fixed crash on 'reader.connect()' if the tag is gone.

Fixed the GPB of the factory format function.

The General purpose byte (GPB) is important for the
Mifare application directory (MAD).

Fix for language independent dumps.

Added some suff for later use (diplay in dump editor if a
sector could not be read).

Show sectors that could not be read.

The information about unreadable sectors will be
cleand on 'update colors' and on 'save dump'.
A saved dump never contains informaiton abount unreadable sectors.

New release: 1.5.1

Updated changelog.
Increased version number.
